<h2 id="post-116"><a href="http://dirk-kutscher.info/publications/ietf/decade-architecture-2/" rel="bookmark">DECADE Architecture</a></h2>
<p class="comments"><a href="http://dirk-kutscher.info/publications/ietf/decade-architecture-2/#comments">without comments</a></p>

<div class="main">
	<p>We have submitted a new version of the DECADE architecture draft, which is now a work item of the <a href="https://datatracker.ietf.org/wg/decade/charter/">IETF DECADE WG</a>.</p>
<p><strong>Abstract:</strong><br />
Peer-to-peer (P2P) applications have become widely used on the<br />
Internet today and make up a large portion of the traffic in many<br />
networks.  One technique to improve the network efficiency of P2P<br />
applications is to introduce storage capabilities within the<br />
networks.  The DECADE Working Group has been formed with the goal of<br />
developing an architecture to provide this capability.  This document<br />
presents an architecture, discusses the underlying principles, and<br />
identifies core components and protocols supporting the architecture.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>The Internet Draft: <a href="http://datatracker.ietf.org/doc/draft-ietf-decade-arch/">draft-ietf-decade-arch</a></p>
</div>

<div class="meta group">
<div class="signature">
    <p>Written by dkutscher <span class="edit"></span></p>
    <p>März 9th, 2011 at 3:13 pm</p>
</div>	
